e thieves) washed up on a seashore somewhere. The Demon King Howard has kidnapped Trezno for his own nefarious plans and the rest of the thieves must stop his evolving plan.","collection":1993,"popularity":1.0,"games":[12632,36926,27209,11214,28010,36608,19333,47823,26766,16468],"tags":[1,268435468,536870990,536871139,536871208,536871938,536872594],"category":0,"keywords":[78,227,296,1026,1682],"themes":[1],"genres":[12],"first_release_date":801014400000,"platforms":[19],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":19,"date":801014400000,"region":8,"human":"1995-May-21","y":1995,"m":5}],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/zkzmo7vm4d3uvhi83xjp.jpg","cloudinary_id":"zkzmo7vm4d3uvhi83xjp","width":609,"height":1115}},{"id":42289,"name":"Ihatovo Monogatari","slug":"ihatovo-monogatari","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/ihatovo-monogatari","created_at":1499071442917,"updated_at":1515657541141,"summary":"The story depicts the action as taking place in the utopian world of Ihatovo. \n \nThe game focuses on collecting information (notebooks from Miyazawa's fairy tales) and items (that are related to those fairy tales) instead of fighting monsters. Some of the surprises that the player finds includes a movie theater that is always closed, the opportunity to play the role of a temporary school teacher, and having portraits of unique non-player characters that show up while talking to them. \n \nInspired by the stories of Kenji Miyazawa, the story covers nine chapters and surreal environments. The ending involves speaking to Mr. Miyazawa himself and returning to the real world via the Galaxy Express train.","collection":3736,"popularity":1.0,"games":[26766,36926,36534,18398,13189,25222,41895,22425,55803,19448],"tags":[268435487,536871208,536871938,536871939,536875057,536875181,536879119],"category":0,"keywords":[296,1026,1027,4145,4269,8207],"genres":[31],"first_release_date":733968000000,"platforms":[19],"release_dates":[{"category":0,"platform":19,"date":7