mbling rocks \nClassic platforming fun","popularity":1.333333333333333,"games":[55752,28154,63138,19174,10039,22425,1070,36868,41064,18927],"tags":[268435464,536870947,536872475,536872961,536875271,536875437,536875822,536875952],"category":0,"keywords":[35,1563,2049,4359,4525,4910,5040],"genres":[8],"cover":{"url":"//images.igdb.com/igdb/image/upload/t_thumb/ajwvocwz3u7w2pvdahhi.jpg","cloudinary_id":"ajwvocwz3u7w2pvdahhi","width":400,"height":359},"esrb":{"rating":3}},{"id":43573,"name":"Disney's Peter Pan: The Legend of Neverland","slug":"disneys-peter-pan-the-legend-of-neverland","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/disneys-peter-pan-the-legend-of-neverland","created_at":1499155960474,"updated_at":1500544266597,"summary":"Swashbuckle your way through hoardes of pirates and evil enemies \nFree your kidnapped friends and find the hidden pixie dust \nTrack down Captain Hook in a final duel to decide the fate of Never Land itself","popularity":1.333333333333333,"category":0},{"id":43574,"name":"The Show MLB 08 - duplicate","slug":"the-show-mlb-08-duplicate","url":"https://www.igdb.com/games/the-show-mlb-08-duplicate","created_at":1499155962560,"updated_at":1510083710497,"summary":"MLB 08: The Show is a baseball simulation video game developed by SCE San Diego Studio published by Sony Computer Entertainment for the PlayStation 2, PlayStation 3, and PlayStation Portable systems. It is the longest-running officially licensed Major League Baseball game series on the PlayStation systems.[1] MLB 08: The Show is the third edition of the MLB: The Show series of video games. The game was announced for all three PlayStation consoles on December 11, 2007,[2] and released on March 4, 2008 in North America.[1] Ryan Howard, all-star first baseman for the Philadelphia Phillies, is featured as the game's cover athlete.[3] \n \nThe game is a baseball simulation in which, depending on the gameplay mode, the player controls one or all of the players on a Major League Baseball team or some 